<item>
            <title>[MATH-965] Inconsistency between the init method and the other ones in step and event handlers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-965</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The EventHandler and StepHandler interfaces allow user code to be called by ODE integrators at some points. Both interfaces provide an &quot;init&quot; method which get the initial state as a double array &quot;y0&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
The &quot;g&quot; and &quot;eventOccurred&quot; methods also get a double array &quot;y&quot; corresponding to current state. The size of the array in these two methods correspond only to the primary state whereas in the &quot;init&quot; methods it holds both the primary state and the secondary states.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be better to always provide the complete state (primary and secondary) in all methods, so users can also trigger events based on secondary states.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
